Lf at pH 9.0 (Figure 4.1) that shows the start of the thermal denaturation of the protein at 

56 °C. In addition, the max in the thermally denatured Lf at 80°C is higher than the max 

in the Lf denatured by SDS ([SDS] > 2.6 mM) indicating that: (i) the thermally denatured 

Lf structure is different from that denatured by SDS; (ii) SDS decreases the solvent 



