solution up to the surfactant concentration attain C2, ? +  is the energy of 
demicellization and dilution of the monomers obtained from premicelar region in the 

surfactant dilution curve, Y is the number of injections necessary to C2 be attained, Vy is 

the total volume in the calorimetric cell at C2, and ninj is the number of moles of surfactant 

injected in each injection. 

